Instructions
1. Install mkfilelink.bat and mkfolderlink.bat to C:\Windows\system.
2. Double-click each of the .reg files.
3. Done!

Notes
* The link is created in the parent directory of the link target so that you do not have to rename it.
* Ipso facto, you cannot create links of top-level folders such as Program Files.
* Hard links are not yet supported.
* Junctions (cross-drive links) are not yet supported.